Taiwan Plans 15% Property-Speculation Tax, Economic Daily Says

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-02-24T22:31:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/taiwan-plans-15-property-speculation-tax-economic-daily-says.html
Taiwan’s ministry of finance plans
to impose a 15 percent transaction tax on unoccupied dwellings
sold within a year of purchase, and 10 percent sold after one to
two years, to curb property speculation, the Economic Daily News
reported today, citing ministry sources it didn’t identify.
Finance Minister Lee Sush-der met with President Ma Ying-jeou
yesterday to outline the proposals, which include a tax on  luxury goods , including cars over NT$3 million, and furs over
NT$500,000, the newspaper reported.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
